The named person must carry ID as proof of identity.</p></li><li><p>During any match, the named (responsible) person must accompany the Junior/Intermediate angler throughout the duration of the match and at no time must the Junior/Intermediate be left unsupervised.</p></li><li><p>The named person attending the match is totally responsible for the persons in their charge.</p></li><li><p>No Junior/Intermediate can enter any match pools in either Junior or Senior matches.</p></li><li><p>A series of matches, with no entry fee, are fished each year for trophies. Non-cash prizes will be awarded.</p></li><li><p>Casting can be done by the accompanying adult, but the rod must then be immediately passed to the junior angler:</p></li><li><p>There are no feeding restrictions concerning the adult.</p></"},{"LineNumber":3242,"AttributeName":"Body","AttributeValue":"1~|li><li><p>When reeling in and landing a fish ALL juniors must have one hand on the rod with their other hand on the reel. An adult may only help by the supporting of and the raising of the rod itself and may assist with all aspects of netting and unhooking of the fish.</p></li><li><p>ANY fish hooked by an adult MUST be immediately and freely returned to the water.</p></li><li><p>Rules for Potters Pond matches:</p><p>- Barbless hooks only & NO ground bait</p></li></ol>"},{"LineNumber":3243,"AttributeName":"RuleType","AttributeValue":"3"},{"LineNumber":3244,"AttributeName":"Title","AttributeValue":"Junior / Intermediate Member - Match Rules"},{"LineNumber":3245,"AttributeName":"dbKey","AttributeValue":"Rules:60efdcb7-fc98-4853-9e47-2bd10e747a85"},{"LineNumber":3246,"AttributeName":"Body","AttributeValue":"0~|<p><b>Membership for Juniors is FREE up to the age of 12 years.</b></p><ol><li><p>A Junior/Intermediate disclosure form must be completed. when applying for club membership. No disclosure form - no membership.</p></li><li><p>All juniors must be accompanied by a nominated person or persons from their disclosure form whilst fishing at the following venues:</p><p>- Ellenthorpe Hall</p><p>- Ellenthorpe Lodge</p><p>- Roecliffe Ponds</p><p>This rule must apply for the duration of the time spent fishing on any one day.</p></li><li><p>A Junior/Intermediate member is classed as a junior up to the 1st of April following their 16th birthday. On 1st April after their 16th birthday, they will be classed as an Intermediate up to the 1st January following their 18th birthday.</p></li><li><p>Parents of Junior/Intermediate members must purchase a key for the Roecliffe Pond gate. Failure to do so will result in immediate expulsion from the club for the remainder of that year. An excluded member will have to apply to the committee for new membership, on which a vote will be taken.</p></li><li><p>All subscription renewals will be due 1st April. All fish to be returned alive.</p></li><li><p>All live fish weigh, with the exception of pike and game fish.</p></li><li><p>Competitors may assist each other in netting or landing fish.</p></li><li><p>Before the starting signal no competitor must on any account, ground bait or loose feed his swim, but will be allowed to wet a line, plumb the depth and test the float, mix ground bait, clear his fishing ground of weed or obstructions and position his keep net."},{"LineNumber":3260,"AttributeName":"Body","AttributeValue":"1~| On no account must a feeder be used to plumb the depth before the starting signal.</p></li><li><p>Competitors must fish at peg drawn and under no circumstances be allowed to change pegs.</p></li><li><p>Competitors must not move more than one yard each side of their peg to fish.
